==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tarsometatarsus
<hw>Tar`so*met`a*tar"sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Tarsometatarsi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The large bone next the foot in
the leg of a bird. It is formed by the union of the distal part of the
tarsus with the metatarsus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarsorrhaphy</ent>⟦br⟧
